==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: chelating agent
<hw>che"lat*ing a`gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>a compound which forms a chelate with a metal
ion.</def> <note>Commonly used chelating agents in laboratory use are
<stype>EDTA</stype> and <stype>sodium citrate</stype>. Citrate is used
as an additive to blood collected in blood banks, to chelate the calcium
ions and retard clotting.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>chelation</ent>⟦br⟧
